x = "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zürich";
請參閱 http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=761051。
x = "file:///foo.bar";
x = "file://c:/foo.bar";
x = "file://shäres/foo.bar";
Some text, then http://www.bing.com.
```

Generating a JSDoc comment for a variable/constant should generate an @type annotation
```js
/** |
var p;
```

Inserts

```js
/**
 * @type {any}
 */
var p;
```

In the following generated JS Doc comment I would have expected that there is also a `@returns` comment.
 
```js
/**
 * 
 * @param {any} a
 * @param {any} b
 */
function foo(a, b) {
  return 12;
}
```

I would be nice when the generated JSDoc comment is a snippet to that I can tab to the `{any}` place holders (see below).

```js
/**
 * 
 * @param {any} a
 * @param {any} b
 */
function foo(a, b) {
  return true;
}
```
